adGenAOS3GMib.name: adGenAOS3GMib

revisions.description: Added TEXTUAL-CONVENTION EcioValue and object identifier adGenAOS3GECIOIntegerValue. Changes by Reba Holland.
Changed syntax of object identifier adGenAOS3GECIOIntegerValue from EcioValue to Integer32. Removed TEXTUAL CONVENTION EcioValue. Changes by Reba Holland.

adGenAOS3GMib.contactinfo: Technical Support Dept. Postal: ADTRAN, Inc. 901 Explorer Blvd. Huntsville, AL 35806 Tel: +1 800 726-8663 Fax: +1 256 963 6217 E-mail: support@adtran.com
adGenAOS3GMib.description: A MIB module for monitoring 3G module values.

adGenAOS3GTraps.name: adGenAOS3GTraps
adGenAOS3GTraps.description: The table contains traps/alarms caused by changes in configuration values and when statistical data reach certain thresholds.

adGenAOS3GTable.name: adGenAOS3GTable
adGenAOS3GTable.description: The table contains 3G cellular statistical data for the cellular interface.

adGenAOS3GEntry.name: adGenAOS3GEntry
adGenAOS3GEntry.description: This is an entry into the 3G table.

adGenAOS3GNetworkAccessID.name: adGenAOS3GNetworkAccessID
adGenAOS3GNetworkAccessID.description: The Network Access ID is the User ID submitted by the 3G Modem during Mobile IP authentication. For more information, refer to RFC 4282.

adGenAOS3GHASS.name: adGenAOS3GHASS
adGenAOS3GHASS.description: This OID displays whether the shared secret for the home agent has been set for Mobile IP authentication.

adGenAOS3GHASPI.name: adGenAOS3GHASPI
adGenAOS3GHASPI.description: The Home Agent Security Parameter Index uniquely identifies a security association for the home agent for use during Mobile IP authentication.

adGenAOS3GAAASS.name: adGenAOS3GAAASS
adGenAOS3GAAASS.description: This OID displays whether the shared secret for AAA has been set for Mobile IP authentication.

adGenAOS3GAAASPI.name: adGenAOS3GAAASPI
adGenAOS3GAAASPI.description: The AAA Security Parameter Index uniquely identifies a security association for AAA for use during Mobile IP authentication.

adGenAOS3GReverseTunneling.name: adGenAOS3GReverseTunneling
adGenAOS3GReverseTunneling.description: This OID describes if a tunnel is setup from the 3G module's care of address to the home agent. A care of address is a temporary IP address for a mobile device.

adGenAOS3GHomeAddress.name: adGenAOS3GHomeAddress
adGenAOS3GHomeAddress.description: The permanent home IP address for the 3G module in the cellular network.

adGenAOS3GPrimaryHomeAddress.name: adGenAOS3GPrimaryHomeAddress
adGenAOS3GPrimaryHomeAddress.description: The primary IP address of the 3G module's home agent.

adGenAOS3GSecHomeAddress.name: adGenAOS3GSecHomeAddress
adGenAOS3GSecHomeAddress.description: The secondary IP address of the 3G module's home agent.

adGenAOS3GRSSI.name: adGenAOS3GRSSI
adGenAOS3GRSSI.description: The Receive Signal Strength Indicator for the cellular connection. This value is a measurement of signal strength.

adGenAOS3GECIO.name: adGenAOS3GECIO
adGenAOS3GECIO.description: The Ec/Io for the cellular connection. This is the ratio of received pilot energy to the total received energy. The value is similar to signal-to-noise ratio.

adGenAOS3GPnOffset.name: adGenAOS3GPnOffset
adGenAOS3GPnOffset.description: The Pn Offset for the cellular connection. Base stations assigned to a particular frequency carrier operate at the same center frequency. The PN offset is used to distinguish base stations from one another.

adGenAOS3GServiceType.name: adGenAOS3GServiceType
adGenAOS3GServiceType.description: The current Cellular Service Type for the cellular connection.

adGenAOS3GServiceTypePreference.name: adGenAOS3GServiceTypePreference
adGenAOS3GServiceTypePreference.description: The current Cellular Service Type Preference for the cellular connection. Cellular Service Type can be forced to 1xRTT mode or 1xEVDO mode. By default, it is set to Hybrid or AUTO mode which chooses the best available signal.

adGenAOS3GConnectionState.name: adGenAOS3GConnectionState
adGenAOS3GConnectionState.description: The current Connection State for the cellular connection.

adGenAOS3GECIOIntegerValue.name: adGenAOS3GECIOIntegerValue
adGenAOS3GECIOIntegerValue.description: The Ec/Io for the cellular connection displayed in integer form. This is the ratio of received pilot energy to the total received energy. The value is similar to signal-to-noise ratio. EC/IO values typically are represented as a value with a decimal place. In this representation the value will be scaled by 10. Hence a value of 1.5 will be represented as 15.

adGenAOS3GHardwareDataTable.name: adGenAOS3GHardwareDataTable
adGenAOS3GHardwareDataTable.description: The table contains profile information for the 3G cellular interface.

adGenAOS3GHardwareDataEntry.name: adGenAOS3GHardwareDataEntry
adGenAOS3GHardwareDataEntry.description: This is an entry into the 3G hardware data table.

adGenAOS3GSystemID.name: adGenAOS3GSystemID
adGenAOS3GSystemID.description: The System Identification number is the identifier for a cellular network in a certain area.

adGenAOS3GNetworkID.name: adGenAOS3GNetworkID
adGenAOS3GNetworkID.description: The Network Identification number identifies a subset of a particular SID corresponding to different networks.

adGenAOS3GPrefferedRoamList.name: adGenAOS3GPrefferedRoamList
adGenAOS3GPrefferedRoamList.description: The PRL is a database of cell towers that the cellular modem can roam on. This OID specifies the current version of that database that is programmed onto the cellular modem.

adGenAOS3GMobileDirNumber.name: adGenAOS3GMobileDirNumber
adGenAOS3GMobileDirNumber.description: The MDN is the 10 digit phone number assigned to the 3G module.

adGenAOS3GESN.name: adGenAOS3GESN
adGenAOS3GESN.description: The Electronic Serial Number is is a unique number that identifies the 3G module.

adGenAOS3GMobileStationID.name: adGenAOS3GMobileStationID
adGenAOS3GMobileStationID.description: The MSID is a 10 digit number that identifies the 3G module in the network.

adGenAOS3GHardwareVersion.name: adGenAOS3GHardwareVersion
adGenAOS3GHardwareVersion.description: The hardware version of the 3G modem.

adGenAOS3GFirmwareVersion.name: adGenAOS3GFirmwareVersion
adGenAOS3GFirmwareVersion.description: The firmware version of the 3G modem.

adGenAOS3GThresholdDataTable.name: adGenAOS3GThresholdDataTable
adGenAOS3GThresholdDataTable.description: The table contains settings regarding whether the trap is enabled and threshold values for certain traps.

adGenAOS3GThresholdDataEntry.name: adGenAOS3GThresholdDataEntry
adGenAOS3GThresholdDataEntry.description: This is an entry into the 3G threshold data table.

adGenAOS3GEnableTraps.name: adGenAOS3GEnableTraps
adGenAOS3GEnableTraps.description: This OID indicates whether traps are enabled for the interface.

adGenAOS3GRSSIThreshold.name: adGenAOS3GRSSIThreshold
adGenAOS3GRSSIThreshold.description: This is a value from (-200..200) that sets the threshold for an RSSI trap to occur. When the RSSI is below this value, it will cause an RSSI alarm trap. When the RSSI rises above this value, it will cause an RSSI cleared trap.

adGenAOS3GECIOThreshold.name: adGenAOS3GECIOThreshold
adGenAOS3GECIOThreshold.description: This is a value from (-200..200) that sets the threshold for an ECIO trap to occur. When the ECIO is below this value, it will cause an ECIO alarm trap. When the ECIO rises above this value, it will cause an ECIO cleared trap.

rssiDataRangeAlarm.name: rssiDataRangeAlarm
rssiDataRangeAlarm.description: This trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the RSSI data value object for the 3G cellular interface has exceeded the range specified by the user.

ecioDataRangeAlarm.name: ecioDataRangeAlarm
ecioDataRangeAlarm.description: This trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the ECIO data value object for the 3G cellular interface has exceeded the range specified by the user.

rssiDataRangeClear.name: rssiDataRangeClear
rssiDataRangeClear.description: This trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the RSSI data value object for the 3G cellular interface has returned to the range specified by the user.

ecioDataRangeClear.name: ecioDataRangeClear
ecioDataRangeClear.description: This trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the ECIO data value object for the 3G cellular interface has returned to the range specified by the user.

configValueSet.name: configValueSet
configValueSet.description: This trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that a data value object for the 3G cellular interface from the 3G Hardware Table has been modified from the previous state.

modemResetAlarm.name: modemResetAlarm
modemResetAlarm.description: This trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the 3G modem has been reset.

serviceTypeChangeAlarm.name: serviceTypeChangeAlarm
serviceTypeChangeAlarm.description: This trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the service type for the 3G cellular interface has changed.

connectionStateDownAlarm.name: connectionStateDownAlarm
connectionStateDownAlarm.description: This trap signifies that the SNMP entity, acting in an agent role, has detected that the connection status of the modem has gone down from either DORMANT or a CONNECTED state.

adGenAOS3GFullCompliance.name: adGenAOS3GFullCompliance
adGenAOS3GFullCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement version 2 of the adGenAOS3G MIB.

adGenAOS3GTableGroup.name: adGenAOS3GTableGroup
adGenAOS3GTableGroup.description: This group contains 3G cellular statistical data for profile information.

adGenAOS3GHardwareDataGroup.name: adGenAOS3GHardwareDataGroup
adGenAOS3GHardwareDataGroup.description: This group contains 3G cellular statistical data for hardware information.

adGenAOS3GThresholdDataGroup.name: adGenAOS3GThresholdDataGroup
adGenAOS3GThresholdDataGroup.description: This group contains threshold data for enabling 3G interface thresholds.

adGenAOS3GTrapGroup.name: adGenAOS3GTrapGroup
adGenAOS3GTrapGroup.description: Traps which may be used to enhance event driven management of the interface.
